{"type":"message","id":"38183d9c","parentId":"5c37a6f6","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:27:43.835Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory doesn't have a heartbeat-state.json, so there's no prior state to compare against. Let me check if there's a baseline stored elsewhere or in memory.\n\nActually, looking at the sessions_list output and the previous cycles' system messages in the main session history, I can reconstruct the baseline:\n\n**Baseline (from last known stable cycles):**\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p) ✅ running\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) ✅ running\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) ✅ running\n\n\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` (QLHV group) ✅ running\n- `telegram:group:-5168104492` (DTLX group) ✅ done\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` (Lead direct) ✅ done\n- `main` ✅ done\n- Pre-existing zombies: `b653a6c0`, `ac986a8d`\n\nNow checking the current state at 15:26 UTC. I'm noticing some session key inconsistencies across different timestamps—`cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` appeared in the 15:20 UTC report but earlier entries showed just `cron:e7885813`. Looking at the 15:25 UTC session list, I'm seeing different session IDs like `972d6601-ee07-44cc-8674-9be1d2b52857` and `6e4eca8a-e041-42f8-90e1-d29f47b9c7ff`, so I need to reconcile these variations with what's actually in the current sessions_list.\n\nComparing the baseline against what's currently running, I can see the DTLX and QLHV cron jobs are still active, but the Agent Status session shows a new ID with an updated timestamp. The QLHV group session is also running with a different ID than before. The DTLX group session is still marked as done from the baseline.\n\nLooking at the Lead direct and main sessions, those are also showing as done, which is consistent with the baseline. The agent status session just refreshed its ID, which isn't really a change in the system's overall health—just a timing artifact from when the cron job ran.\n\nSo comparing everything across both timeframes, the critical sessions that matter are all running as expected: the two cron jobs and the two Telegram groups are all still active. The zombie sessions are unchanged from before, so there's no real state transition to report here. No change detected. Silent exit.","thinkingSignature":"6cc7d3c511c937dd65a80ec13aa081f880177dce49fd865c378550691a28a53d"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (15:26 UTC) against baseline (15:10 UTC):\n\n**Baseline (15:10 UTC):**\n- `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ `cron:e7885813` ✅ `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅ `telegram:group:-5168104492` ✅ `telegram:direct:6053576134` ✅ `main` ✅\n\n**Current (15:26 UTC):**\n- `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ `cron:e7885813` ✅ `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅ `telegram:group:-5168104492` ✅ `telegram:direct:6053576134` ✅ `main` ✅\n\nAll sessions match baseline. No state transitions, no failures, no blockers. Silent exit."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":17322,"output":745,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":411,"totalTokens":32422,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776180446508,"responseId":"062d8fe0dbbe050e6eed6ba4c3a0ae28"}}
